# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Types:
#   feat     (new feature for the user, not a new feature for build script)
#   fix      (bug fix for the user, not a fix to a build script)
#   docs     (changes to the documentation)
#   style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no production code change)
#   refactor (refactoring production code, eg. renaming a variable)
#   test     (adding missing tests, refactoring tests; no production code change)
#   chore    (updating grunt tasks etc; no production code change)
#   perf     (performance improvements)
#   ci       (changes to CI configuration files and scripts)
#   build    (changes that affect the build system or external dependencies)
#   revert   (revert a previous commit)

# Scopes:
#   api      (API related changes)
#   auth     (authentication related changes)
#   ui       (user interface changes)
#   db       (database related changes)
#   test     (test related changes)
#   docs     (documentation changes)
#   deps     (dependency updates)
#   config   (configuration changes)
#   ci       (CI/CD changes)
#   build    (build system changes)

# Subject:
#   - use imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
#   - don't capitalize first letter
#   - no dot (.) at the end

# Body:
#   - use imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
#   - include motivation for the change and contrast with previous behavior

# Footer:
#   - Breaking changes should start with "BREAKING CHANGE: "
#   - Issues should be referenced by their number, e.g. "Closes #123"
#   - Co-authored-by: for co-authors

# Examples:
#   feat(auth): add OAuth2 authentication
#
#   Implement OAuth2 authentication using Google and GitHub providers.
#   This allows users to sign in with their existing accounts.
#
#   Closes #123
#   Co-authored-by: John Doe <john@example.com>

#   fix(api): resolve user data not loading issue
#
#   The user data was not loading due to incorrect API endpoint.
#   Updated the endpoint to use the correct path.
#
#   Fixes #456

#   docs(readme): update installation instructions
#
#   Added step-by-step installation instructions for new users.
#   Included troubleshooting section for common issues.

#   style(ui): format code according to style guide
#
#   Applied consistent formatting to all UI components.
#   No functional changes made.

#   refactor(db): optimize database queries
#
#   Replaced N+1 queries with optimized joins.
#   Improved performance by 50% for user list page.

#   test(auth): add unit tests for authentication
#
#   Added comprehensive unit tests for OAuth2 authentication.
#   Coverage increased to 95% for auth module.

#   chore(deps): update dependencies to latest versions
#
#   Updated all dependencies to their latest stable versions.
#   No breaking changes introduced.

#   perf(api): optimize API response time
#
#   Implemented caching layer for frequently accessed data.
#   Reduced average response time from 200ms to 50ms.

#   ci(build): add automated testing pipeline
#
#   Added GitHub Actions workflow for automated testing.
#   Tests run on every push and pull request.

#   build(deps): update webpack configuration
#
#   Updated webpack configuration for better tree shaking.
#   Reduced bundle size by 30%.

#   revert(api): revert breaking API changes
#
#   Reverted API changes that caused client compatibility issues.
#   Will re-implement with proper versioning in next release.
#
#   Reverts #789 